<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="299" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Genetic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">
We successfully barcoded six of the seven collected grunt species viz. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Satapoomin et Randall" authorityYear="2000" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus macrospilus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrospilus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus macrospilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McKay et Satapoomin" authorityYear="1994" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys andamanensis" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="andamanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys andamanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1833" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys argyreus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="argyreus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys argyreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys guoraca" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guoraca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys guoraca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bloch" baseAuthorityYear="1793" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys maculatus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and submitted to GenBank (NCBI) and BOLD system. The COI sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Satapoomin et Randall" authorityYear="2000" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus macrospilus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrospilus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus macrospilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McKay et Satapoomin" authorityYear="1994" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys andamanensis" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="andamanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys andamanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys guoraca" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guoraca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys guoraca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were submitted for the first time to GenBank as reference DNA barcode sequence. We identified 11 COI barcode sequences of 6 species. For 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pomadasys argenteus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="argenteus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Pomadasys argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we were unable to obtain a clear sequence. Sequence alignment of COI gene yielded about 602 nucleotide base pairs after removing the ambiguous sequences near primer ends. The COI sequences of 11 individuals of 6 species comprised 11 haplotypes with 174 polymorphic sites. The estimated mean ratio of transition and transversion was 2.88. The sequence analysis revealed that the mean nucleotide compositions in 11 COI sequences of 6 species were A = 22.5% 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.52%, T = 28.11% 
